NAME
    Regexp::ID::NumVerbage - Regex pattern to match Indonesian number
    verbage in text

VERSION
    version 0.01

SYNOPSIS
     use Regexp::ID::NumVerbage ($RE);

     say $1 if "pemasukan tahun ini mencapai tiga koma tujuh triliun" =~ /\b($RE)\b/; # "tiga koma tujuh triliun"

EXPORTS
  $RE (regex)
    A regex for quickly matching/extracting verbage from text; it looks for
    a string of words. It's not perfect (the extracted verbage might not be
    valid, e.g. "dua ratus tiga ribu"), but it's convenient.

SEE ALSO
    Regexp::EN::NumVerbage.

